message.content:
Before breaking his right arm, Cam could type 9 words per minute. In 5 minutes, he would be able to type 9 x 5 = 45 words.

After breaking his right arm and using his left hand, Cam could only type 6 words per minute. In 5 minutes, he would be able to type 6 x 5 = 30 words.

The difference in the number of words typed in 5 minutes is:
45 words (before) - 30 words (after) = 15 words.

So Cam was able to type 15 more words per minute before he broke his right arm, than after he broke it and had to use his left hand for a while.
